---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Work Forest">
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Work Forest</h1>
    <p class="tagline">A pattern for parallel AI-assisted development</p>
    <p class="note">Not a tool—just ideas you can use with git and any AI agent.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="idea">
    <h2>The Idea</h2>
    <p>Instead of one agent working on one thing, create multiple worktrees and let agents work in parallel:</p>
    <pre><code>project/              # main branch (read-only)
project-feature-a/    # agent 1 works here
project-feature-b/    # agent 2 works here
project-bugfix/       # agent 3 works here</code></pre>
    <p>Each worktree is isolated. No merge conflicts during development. Integrate when ready.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="clusters">
    <h2>Work Clusters</h2>
    <p>Split big tasks into semantic pieces. Just ask:</p>
    <blockquote>"Build auth. Backend, frontend, database. Work in parallel, then integrate."</blockquote>
    <p>Claude spawns sub-agents for each cluster, then merges everything.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="plans">
    <h2>Planning Documents</h2>
    <p>Plans live in files with unique IDs. Context survives session resets:</p>
    <pre><code>plans/
├── 3el7f-auth-refactor.md
├── 9xk2m-api-redesign.md
└── w7bn4-mobile-support.md</code></pre>
    <p>The GUID prefix makes plans greppable across your entire workspace. New sessions read the plan file and continue where you left off.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="stacked">
    <h2>Stacked PRs</h2>
    <p>Clean commits, easy reviews:</p>
    <pre><code>main
└── refactor-auth     # PR 1: cleanup only
    └── add-oauth     # PR 2: feature on clean code</code></pre>
    <p>The pattern handles the complexity. You work at the intent level.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="tradeoffs">
    <h2>Trade-offs</h2>
    <p>This isn't magic. Parallel work means integration overhead. Some work may be redundant. You still decide how to split tasks. But you gain higher-level thinking and faster iteration.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <a href="https://github.com/joshribakoff/workforest.space" class="btn" target="_blank">View on GitHub</a>
  </section>
</Base>

